title: Cate Blanchett Performed at a Drag Show Because Her Talent Knows No Limits - Watch Cate Blanchett Perform at a Drag Show
text: Last night, the ever-versatile Cate Blanchett put on the performance we didn't know we needed when she made a cameo at a drag show at New York's historic gay bar, The Stonewall Inn. The actress took a break from her Ocean's Eight filming duties and participated in a benefit performance, where she took part in two musical numbers. The first was a solo lip-synced rendition of Leslie Gore's "You Don't Own Me," which Blanchett took on Cabaret -style (watch out, Liza Minnelli), in a glittery leotard, blazer, dangling earrings, bejeweled red lips and the perfect amount of sass. Naturally, the audience went wild.
